Kotthaus Says Will Wait for For EBA Proposals on Recapitalizing

-- B y   P a t r i c k   D o n a h u e
-- 
2011-10-12T10:02:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/kotthaus-says-will-wait-for-for-eba-proposals-on-recapitalizing.html
Germany  is awaiting proposals from
the European Union’s top banking regulator, the European Banking
Authority, before it moves ahead with details of a plan to
recapitalize the region’s banks, Finance Ministry spokesman
Martin Kotthaus told reporters today in Berlin.  Banks should use their own means to recapitalize at first
and be equipped for “all eventualities,” Kotthaus said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Patrick Donahue at 
 pdonahue1@bloomberg.net  